 :tx/rationale "Create task: EPIC: Store-Codebase Observability — trace staleness detection + comprehensive scanning (Proposals 3, 6). BACKGROUND: The store's :impl/implements links are snapshots from the last trace scan. Between scans, codebase changes create an observability gap: F(S) underestimates convergence, task audit misses implemented tasks, 115 spec-impl gaps are mostly false positives. ROOT CAUSE: Detection mechanism (trace scanner) exists but only runs at harvest boundaries. The store observes itself perfectly (append-only datoms) but observes the CODEBASE only at scan time. This is Structural Divergence from the reconciliation taxonomy — implementation changed but the store doesn't know. APPROACH: Two-layer fix: (1) Staleness detector: O(n) mtime check per .rs file, displayed in status. (2) Incremental scan: only scan files modified since last scan. Together these make the observability gap VISIBLE and CLOSEABLE. TRACES TO: INV-BILATERAL-002, INV-WITNESS-011, INV-HARVEST-001."
